div.p:
The chief sources of revenue are direct taxes. Land tax, nearly 65 millions;
                    house tax, 23 millions; trade and business taxes, 11 millions; income tax, (7
                    per cent.,) 20½ millions. Total, 119½ millions.

Indirect taxes.—Brandy, 14 millions; wine, 6 millions;
beer, 17 millions; sugar, 9 millions; cattle, to be killed, 5½ millions;
Pachtungon leases, 5 millions; salt, (monopoly,) net receipts, about 33
millions; tobacco, net, 25 millions; stamps, 16½ millions; taxes on legal
business, 26½ millions; lottery, 20 millions; customs, less 1,674,614 for
collection, net almost exactly 12½ millions. Total, 190 millions.
